doc.after: The Australian magpie is almost exclusively diurnal, although it may call into the night, like some other members of the Artamidae.[54] Natural predators of magpies include various species of monitor lizard and the barking owl.[55] Birds are often killed on roads or electrocuted by powerlines, or poisoned after killing and eating house sparrows or mice, rats or rabbits targeted with baiting.[56] The Australian raven may take nestlings left unattended.[57]
